1.content:
Absolutelyheres a tight game plan to let Claude Code analyze your homepage and then redesign it with animated product cards, using MCPs that specialize in web auditing and live-page interaction.

What to install (MCPs that actually help with UI/UX work)

Lighthouse MCP  one-command performance/SEO/PWA audits with Core Web Vitals; perfect for why is this slow / what should I fix first? 
GitHub
+1
playbooks.com
Glama  MCP Hosting Platform

Axe / A11y MCP  automated accessibility scans (WCAG), actionable findings Claude can fix. Multiple maintained implementations exist. 
Deque
GitHub
LobeHub
PulseMCP

Playwright MCP (Microsoft)  lets Claude interact with your page structure via accessibility trees and take precise DOM-aware actions; great for extracting sections, confirming selectors, and validating changes. 
GitHub

Screenshot MCP (Playwright-based)  fast before/after snapshots of your running site or localhost to verify layout and visual diffs. 
LobeHub
Glama  MCP Hosting Platform
PulseMCP

(Optional) Brave Search MCP  quick competitive scans and design inspiration queries without leaving Claude. 
Reddit

You already set up Vercel MCP for deployments; keep that for preview/production push + logs. (It complements the audit/analysis MCPs.)

Install / add commands (Claude Code)

Make sure your Claude Code CLI is up to date first (npm i -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code). Then add servers.

Lighthouse MCP (Node 16+; Chrome/Chromium required):

# Example: priyankark/lighthouse-mcp (any Lighthouse MCP with get_performance_score is fine)
npx -y @priyankark/lighthouse-mcp@latest
# In another terminal, add it to Claude Code (http/SSE endpoint given by the server)
claude mcp add --transport http lighthouse http://localhost:3333


GitHub
playbooks.com
Glama  MCP Hosting Platform

Axe / A11y MCP (choose one):

# PyPI variant (mcp-axe)
pip install mcp-axe
mcp-axe serve --port 4545
claude mcp add --transport http a11y http://localhost:4545


or

# Node variant (a11y-mcp)
npx -y a11y-mcp@latest
claude mcp add --transport http a11y http://localhost:4545


LobeHub
GitHub
Medium

Playwright MCP (Microsoft):

# Start the server (see repo README for port/flags)
npx -y playwright-mcp@latest
claude mcp add --transport http playwright http://localhost:3000


GitHub

Screenshot MCP:

npx -y @bradydouthit/screenshot-mcp@latest
claude mcp add --transport http screenshot http://localhost:4050


LobeHub

(Optional) Brave Search MCP:

npx -y @brave/brave-search-mcp-server
claude mcp add --transport stdio brave npx -- -y @brave/brave-search-mcp-server


Reddit

Use /mcp inside Claude Code to confirm each server is connected and to complete any auth flows.

How to use them together (fast workflow)

Screenshot your current homepage (prod or localhost)  keep as baseline. 
LobeHub

Lighthouse run  get performance, SEO, PWA, and best-practices scores + prioritized fixes. 
GitHub

Axe run  get a11y violations (+ quick-fix suggestions). 
Deque
GitHub

Playwright  let Claude read the accessibility tree / DOM to precisely locate the red-boxed sections you marked for removal/redesign and confirm selectors safely. 
GitHub

Iterate changes  Screenshot again for diff; rerun Lighthouse + Axe to verify improvements. 
GitHub

Do you need a separate agent?

Not really. Claude Code already orchestrates MCP tools inline. You can simulate an agentic loop by asking Claude to:

run Lighthouse/Axe  summarize issues  propose code  apply diffs  re-run audits.
If you later want a more autonomous loop, add a thin script or use a workflow runner, but you dont need it to get excellent results today. 
Anthropic

Drop-in Final Prompt for the redesign

Paste this as your message in Claude Code (after the MCPs are connected). Replace the URL and file paths where noted.

Role: You are a senior Frontend/UX engineer and design systems lead. You will analyze my homepage and produce a production-ready redesign and code diffs.
Context/Goals:

Site URL (prod or http://localhost:3000): <YOUR_URL_HERE>

There are several sections outlined with red squares in my current design. Delete or completely redesign those sections now.

I need at least 4 product cards that are visually stunning with React + Framer Motion micro-interactions (hover, reveal, subtle parallax/tilt, entrance animations), TailwindCSS, and semantic HTML. Cards must be responsive, keyboard-navigable, and meet WCAG 2.1 AA.

Keep the overall brand vibe (Moonlight Analytica minimal, modern).

Generate mobile-first markup and styles.

Targets: Lighthouse  95 Perf / 100 SEO / 100 Best Practices on mobile test; fix all Axe critical/serious issues; ship with basic SEO (title/meta/OG), schema.org Product markup, and image alt.

Tools available (MCP): Lighthouse, Axe, Playwright, Screenshot, Vercel.

Plan (execute step-by-step and show me results between steps):

Screenshot current homepage, save as /tmp/homepage-before.png.

Run Lighthouse (mobile emulation) on the homepage. Summarize top issues + quick wins (render-blocking, font loading, image formats, CLS culprits).

Run Axe on the homepage. Summarize violations with selectors, why it matters, and fix snippets.

Use Playwright to:

Extract the DOM structure and locate elements corresponding to my red-boxed areas; confirm the selectors you will remove/replace.

Identify where to insert the new 4-card product grid.

Propose a new IA/wireframe (sections order, headings). Then produce the React code:

A self-contained Products.tsx with Framer Motion animations (staggered entrance, hover tilt/reveal), Tailwind classes, and ARIA labels.

A refactor of the page (e.g., app/page.tsx or src/pages/index.tsx) removing/redesigning all red-boxed areas.

Ensure cards have: title, short description, CTA, small tag list, optional badge; prefers reduced motion when prefers-reduced-motion is set.

Generate diffs/patches only (no unrelated files). Include any Tailwind config additions if needed.

Re-run Axe and Lighthouse. Report new scores and remaining gaps.

Screenshot again as /tmp/homepage-after.png. Show a before/after summary (pixels, CLS fixes, bundle size impact).

Prepare a commit message and Vercel deploy instructions.

Acceptance criteria:

Red-boxed sections are deleted or redesigned.

4 animated product cards look premium, feel fast, and are fully accessible.

Mobile Lighthouse  95 Perf; all critical/serious Axe issues resolved.

Clear diffs and instructions to deploy on Vercel.

Now run Step 1 and show me the /tmp/homepage-before.png screenshot. Then proceed step-by-step.

Handy commands to kick off inside Claude Code

After pasting the prompt above:

Use Screenshot MCP to capture the homepage now. 
LobeHub

Run Lighthouse on the homepage (mobile). Paste key metrics + recommendations. 
GitHub

Run Axe and list violations grouped by severity with selectors. 
GitHub

Use Playwright MCP to confirm selectors for the red-boxed areas and proposed insertion point for the product grid. 
GitHub

What you just installed (and why its different)

Vercel MCP is Vercels official hosted MCP server at https://mcp.vercel.com, now in Public Beta, reviewed to work with clients including Claude Code. It uses MCP Authorization + Streamable HTTP and supports OAuth. 
Vercel

Anthropics guide documents the exact Claude Code commands for adding remote HTTP MCP servers (including the Vercel example). 
Anthropic

Common problems & fast fixes

Needs login or stuck auth loop
Run /mcp inside Claude Code to kick off OAuth again and complete the browser flow. If youre in WSL, make sure browser popping to Windows is allowed.

Project slug and Team slug are required
You added the general endpoint. Re-add with a project-specific URL:
https://mcp.vercel.com/<teamSlug>/<projectSlug> (find slugs in Vercel  Settings). 
Vercel

Wrong team/org authorized
Re-run /mcp, sign out/in, and choose the intended Vercel team during OAuth. (Project-specific URL also reduces this confusion.) 
Vercel

Outdated Claude Code
Update the CLI, then try claude mcp list and re-add. 
Anthropic

# Changelog

## 1.0.106

- Windows: Fixed path permission matching to consistently use POSIX format (e.g., `Read(//c/Users/...)`)

## 1.0.97

- Settings: /doctor now validates permission rule syntax and suggests corrections

## 1.0.94

- Vertex: add support for global endpoints for supported models
- /memory command now allows direct editing of all imported memory files
- SDK: Add custom tools as callbacks
- Added /todos command to list current todo items

## 1.0.93

- Windows: Add alt + v shortcut for pasting images from clipboard
- Support NO_PROXY environment variable to bypass proxy for specified hostnames and IPs

## 1.0.90

- Settings file changes take effect immediately - no restart required

## 1.0.88

- Fixed issue causing "OAuth authentication is currently not supported"
